* Unit conversion to an AliasUnit based on CompositeUnit
* Selectable prefix in result
* More functions
* More Units
* Complete number bases
* Approximate variables and exact result (ex. circumference(2) = 2 PI)
* Vector support
* Matrix support
* Fractions
* Derivative, x^2 + y^2 + xy => (x + y)^2, etc.

* Internationalisation
* Separate library
* Support non-glibc systems (Solaris)

* API documentation
* User documentation

* Command line version
* Gnome/KDE applets
* QT version
